The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, February 26, 2003 				 Drive to plug power losses
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Feb. 25: Power minister Anant G. Geete today asked industry to develop and evolve a common communication protocol, standard product specification, open architecture system and innovative metering technologies to bring down the transmission and distribution losses of state electricity boards.																								The minister also called for a total solution for metering, meter reading, billing, and collection with special focus on low cost meters for agricultural customers. He said the products should be flexible enough to enable integration, distribution management, and better customer services. 
